{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> παράδειγ-μα</b>, ατος, τό, <br /> (παραδείκνυμι) <b>pattern, model</b>: of an architect's <b>model</b> (or perhaps <b>plan</b>) of a building, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.62, “IG” 22.1668.95, 11(2).161 A 43,75,203 B 95, +others (Delos, 3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; a sculptor's or painter's <b>model</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 28c, “R.” 500e, “IG” 12.374.248, 22.1675.23 (_plural_) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the divine <b>exemplars</b> after which earthly things are made, ἐν οὐρανῷ ἴσως π. ἀνάκειται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 592b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the Platonic <b>ideas</b>, opposed to εἰκών, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 991a21, 1013a27 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (later, <b>copy</b>, Πλάτων τὸν ὁρατὸν κόσμον γεγονέναι π. τοῦ νοητοῦ κόσμου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Placita Philosophorum” 2.6.4 (variant{πρὸς π}.)). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>precedent, example</b>, παραδείγματα λαβεῖν παρά τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Meno” 77b; ἐμὲ π. ποιούμενος [prev. author] “Ap.” 23b; παραδείγμασι χρῆσθαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. χρῆσθαί τινι copy one's <b>example</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.22; τοῖς γεγενημένοις π. χρῆσθαι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 25.23; π. ἐξοίσετε 4th-3rd c.BC: Dinarchus Orator 1.107; π. καταλείπεσθαι 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 9; δοῦναι παραδείγματα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 876e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ παραδείγματος by way of <b>example</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.177; παραδείγματος εἵνεκα 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 22.20; παραδείγματα ἁμαρτημάτων 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 3.32. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> <b>sample</b>, παραδείγματα νεκρῶν ξύλινα <b>samples</b> of mummies made of wood, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.86, compare “PSI” 5.485 (3rd c.BC), “PCair.Zen.” 445.9, 665.2 (3rd c.BC). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>lesson, warning</b>, ἔχοντες παραδείγματα τῶν ἐκεῖ Ἑλλήνων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.77; τὸ σὸν π. ἔχων 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1193 (Lyric poetry); τοῖς ἄλλοις ἔσται π. ὕβρεως 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 670 (_anapaest meter_); π. καθιστάναι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.40; ζῶντά τινα τοῖς λοιποῖς π. ποιῆσαι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.101, compare 343, 21.98; π. τοὺς Σύρους λαβέ 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 544.1; π. τοῦ μὴ ἀδικεῖν 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 27.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>argument, proof from example</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.2, etc., compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Priora” 68b38, “Rh.” 1356b3, 1402b14, 1418a3, 4th-3rd c.BC: Zeno Citieus Stoicus 1.23\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; including παραβολή and λόγος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1393a 27. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> in Law, <b>leading case, precedent</b>, Wilcken [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Chr.” 27.5 (2nd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>foil, contrast</b>, τὰ γὰρ κακὰ π. τοῖς ἐσθλοῖσιν εἴσοψίν τ᾽ ἔχει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 1085. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8606","accentedUnicode":"παράδειγμα","shortDef":"a model; example; plan","mediumDef":"a model; example; plan","stepGloss":"a model","stepTransliteration":"paradeigma","